loud.name: Romanian solid top Dreadnought = Martin D18
loud.description: This is a REALLY good sounding x commie guitar made in Romania with a solid top, This guitar will hold it's own against vintage MARTIN D18's!!! It is a canon! HERE IS A REVIEW I just received: I have that same model guitar , I have been playing for a very long time and I absolutely love the guitar .I have very fine Martin guitars that are prewar vintage and I find myself reaching for my X-commie most of the time . I perform on stage with my X-commie and it sounds so very , very good . Good luck on your sale I hope someone realizes what a fine guitar it actually is.   Good Luck on your sale .     Chuck  It has a great sound really good action and a nice neck, it looks like the back and sides are maple in any case it has a pretty robust sound for a maple back and sides guitar it's not overly bright and it has a really good bass in addition to a really good treble. Here is part of a Harmony Central (I googled Montana MT-204) review, which I agree completely with:This guitar has incredible sound qualities, from high clear bell like tones to low loud bass and good mid range. i believe it would work well for most any style of music this guitar really projects. everyone who has ever played it has said basically the same thing with a look of surprise, This guitar has great tone! the surprise comes from the fact that nothing about the guitars appearance would suggest that it was anything special.Could DELIVER to greater Rohnert Park Area.

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: 1880's Isidor Lot Wood Flute
famous.description: This flute was made by Isidor Lot, perhaps the nephew of the Famous flutemaker Louis Lotin the 1880's. It is openhole, inline G, C foot and was restored by Daniel Deitch in San Francisco.The sound is warm and sweet and has nothing to do with the volume of the 21st century.It comes in the original case.
